  ----- Original Message -----
  From: Karl von Salzen<mailto:aufever(-at-)hotmail.com>

  Those are the correct specs BUT Bentley neglected to mention that you need
to
  add the 7.5 initial timing to them!  Or if you don't want to do the math,
set
  your timing to zero.

  Advance/Retard Range: Vacuum: 8-12deg Adv (-at-) 7.9 In. Hg; Centrifugal: 9-14deg
(-at-)
  1600 rpm, 21-25deg (-at-) 3400 rpm

  9-14 + 7.5 = 16.5-21.5    Your 19 is right there in the middle.

  21-25 + 7.5 = 28.5-32.5   Your 31 is right where it should be.

  Leave the vacuum hose on and set timing to 7.5. Run it up to 3500-4000 and
  look at the timing. It SHOULD be at the O in VOR!  Which is 100% correct
and
  the way VW designed it. Revving it in neutral is NOT the same as driving it
  down the road under a load. Under a load, vacuum advance goes away when you
go
  past half throttle. Then you have only 31 degrees of advance. Not the 42-45
it
  shows when you rev it.
